  "text": "Emancipative values in sexual freedoms indicate an emancipatory worldview in a broader sense. This conclusion is corroborated by the fact that support for sexual freedoms represents one of four components in [CITATION_1] broader measure of emancipative values. The other components include an emphasis on (a) people's voice, (b) personal autonomy and (c) gender equality and are each measured by three items, as shown in OA 2 (pp. 7-9). At the individual level, emancipative values in sexual freedoms correlate with emancipative values in these other fields significantly and positively at r = .23 (voice), .25 (autonomy) and .33 (equity). The society level correlations are .59, .60 and .73, in the respective order. Nevertheless, support for sexual freedoms sticks out from emancipative values in other domains: it represents an internally more coherent orientation and associates more closely with theoretically expected correlates of an emancipatory worldview.",
